node.text:
I knew very little about negotiation (sorry to all my exes hehe) before reading the bestselling book by @thefbinegotiator. Chris Voss who is a former FBI hostage negotiator and saved many innocent lives purely by talking people out of... their own ideas.

Chris' masterclass is brilliant and a must for those who understand or want to explore the power of non-violent communication. How to let the other side have YOUR way? Keep watching to find out!

#chrisvoss #fbinegotiator #masterclass

node.text:
has nothing to do with travel and doesn't relate to my followers from other countries.

1. Travel is the ultimate privilege of the rich in this world. You may not be rich in your country, but 1 billion people live for less than a $1 a day, more than half live for under $10 day. If you have 'spare' money for recreational travel, you're rich. As a white person, I don't get disrespected or mistaken for a cleaner at a hotel like my friends of color tell me they do on regular basis. The travel blogging industry is predominantly white (and blonde!). The fact you can enter countries, which again a lot of people from different countries can’t say because they will never get a visa is a privilege.

2. Those who tell me this is just an American problem and ‘Americans are so racist’. Easy to point a finger at someone else, but I have never been to a country that wasn't racist. Uk, my native Poland, Australia (Aboriginal people), Brazil, Italy. France... the list goes on. That racism is visible in the police force all around the world, because it's in the air we breathe and in the culture we are surrounded with.

If you're a conscious, open-minded and loving white person, It's time to point a finger at ourselves and say: I want things to be different. People of color need an ally, they need me, they need the white people to speak up. Wherever you are in this world, please share, speak up, be on the humane side of the history, so you can look your grandkids in the eyes and say: I was not silent. #icantbreathe #blacklivesmatter #iwantthingstobedifferent

node.title: For those who tell me that #BLACKLIVESMATTER

node.text:
I recorded this video last Friday and it was scheduled to go live today. I am talking about being a fair weather friend and how in my life, I can deal with haters, but what I struggle with the most is the silence of my ‘friends’.
::::::
Well, this video feels both very inappropriate, because of what happened with #GeorgeFloyd but at the same time also very appropriate, because as a white person, I cannot be silent now. I cannot NOT say something, even all I want to do is cry and say I’m so so so sorry. You DO NOT deserve this. This is so unfair.
:::::::
So I ask all my followers who experienced racism to please record videos of what we (white people who want to help) can do. Post a story and tag me & I will reposting your stories & advice all day today. What do we get wrong? How can we help? Where do we start? We want to learn FROM YOU first hand. I will use my platform today as a megaphone to give the voice to those, whose voice has been ignored for far too long. #icantbreathe

node.title: We'll remember not the words of our enemies, but the silence of our friends

node.text:
'I hit a new rock bottom, where I started asking strangers on the internet what I should do with my life' says @GlennonDoyle in her #1 NYT bestseller UNTAMED.

I love Glennon so much, because she talks about her failures and shame (something I know SO MUCH ABOUT) except Glennon made me realize that that those are things that helped you grow. The moment you (& I) stop trying not to upset people with our behavior, we start living. 
With that said, the entire interview with Glennon will open my @enoughisenough mental health podcast - come check it out! #glennondoyle #untamed #enoughisenough

node.title: Why did you allow yourself to be tamed?

node.text:
After this live with @emma_power, a sexuality & tantra teacher who used to never orgasm, I received hundreds of DMs from women saying they've NEVER had an orgasm during sex￼ (some of them are IG sex symbols, some never orgasmed even with their husbands)

Of course, as typical women, they thought that there was ‘something wrong with them’ and blamed themselves. Not a single one thought: perhaps my man could educate himself a bit 😏 but that’s a topic for another post.

I hesitated for a long time to talk about sex here since there is so much of it online. But there is sex and Sex. The sex that’s predominant on social media is mostly in the context of how to be sexy to attract￼￼ men (a very disempowering context for women)￼ But I wanted to talk about sex as a spiritual experience, a practice where women can be worshiped and celebrated the way they are, regardless of how close their bodies look to insta-perfect. A practice were they feel like empowered goddesses, not sex symbols.

The more we speak up about our standards (regardless if it’s at the office or in the bedroom) and the more we see what’s possible (27 orgasms at a time OR a 4h orgasm! 😋), the more empowered we become as women and that’s why I share this video here.

And to all the men out there committed to their women’s pleasure and taking HOURS not 20 minutes to worship their queens (whether she’s your queen for one night or a lifetime) — Thank you! 
For those happy to learn a thing or two about conscious sex, full interview dropping on YOUTUBE tonight and perhaps more detailed content in the future! More on that soon!

#tantra #tantraislove #womenpower #whorunsthisworld

node.text:
We often don’t have a choice when it comes to what happens to us but we do get to choose the story we tell ourselves about how it shapes us.

Why am I a traveler and a colorist? WHO ELSE COULD I BECOME WITH A MOTHER LIKE THIS?

I love you Mom, your quiet sacrifice has not been left unnoticed. I’m grateful you berated be for calling lilac ‘violet’ and calling crimson ‘red’ 😂 your attention to colors has been the foundation of my career and my success with @aggiepresets - thank you!

Yesterday I was editing photos of my email list peeps live in front of them during my webinar, sign up to my email list to watch a replay! And yes, @colorbundle is still on!!! Winners every day :) #aggiepresets #aggielook #colorbundle #lightroom #loveyoumum

node.title: WE DON’T HAVE A CHOICE, BUT WE DO!

node.text:
In 2011, I bought my first camera, in 2012 I went sailing across the Pacific without any sailing experience.

No phone, no instagram, no followers. Just me, my ex and the biggest ocean on the planet. It took us a year of fighting for our lives to make it back to Sydney from Mexico and it took 8 years for me to publish this video.

I never thought I would ever share it. But with the pandemic around, I see a lot of you struggle with the feeling of ‘life disappearing in front of you’ or not fully enjoying living at home, building your dreams and business and not seeing instant results.

You know what’s the beauty of almost dying? Not dying.

Read that again. I am not ever waiting for a ‘less fun’ period of my life to end to truly live. And ‘truly live’ doesn’t mean disrespecting stay-at-home orders and doing my thing. Not at all. In fact, I have been super diligent about following all the rules, despite the fact that they are super inconvenient and difficult for me.

But f*ck, I almost died once. I will die again. But I will never allow myself to die until I actually die. Over my dead f*cking body. And if I choosing not to die,  I may as well live. Live with a capital L every single day.

Oh and yeah, as far as my story of an overnight 'success' goes? It's taken me almost a decade.

THANK YOU FOR YOU SUPPORT and buying the preset bundle. Your support and love means so much these days!  #pacific #sailing #sailorgirl #travelinhershoes #covid #instantgratification

node.title: The STORY of my 'OVERNIGHT' SUCCESS as a travel writer and ‘influencer’

node.text:
It might not be a popular opinion but I got into traveling to escape the rat race. To pay attention. To listen. And then traveling became a scoreboard of who can produce more content in a shorter amount of time.
:::::
There is no time to learn about new cultures when you go to a new country for three or four days. Traveling became a way to build your ego not to crush it (Which to me is the entire purpose of traveling!).
:::::
I know I’m part of the problem (I am the author of InstaTravel book after all!) so video is as much of a mental note to self as well as the beginning of the conversation about the future of travel. What are your thoughts? #instatravel #travel #travelinhershoes #covid19

node.text:
Full transparency: standing on a side of a helicopter was never my dream 🤷🏼‍♀️

I started skydiving because of and for @jacob. I’d done tandems years before and hated them 😂 but I saw how important skydiving was for J and despite my fear of heights I wanted to give it another go.

And even though I started my skydiving license ‘for’ Jacob, it quickly became not only *my* passion but one of the best things that’s ever happened to *me* (amazing things happen when do things for other people sometimes 😋).

I saw photos like this on Instagram before, each skydiver looking all cool and composed. I’m not either (Someone said the other day I am not a real skydiver because I get scared 😅).

In this photo I am both full of fear but also bursting with pure ‘uncool’ joy.

Joy that comes from conquering a fearful narrative that sometimes stopped me from living my life to the fullest in the past.

The narrative that kinda said: I don’t trust myself to pull the parachute at the right time / and I don’t trust myself doing X, Y & Z in other situations. How disempowering!

Well, yesterday I stood on that ledge and told myself: you got this, Aggie. You can f*cking do this and million other things you never even dreamed of doing.

And I did get it. And you got this too, whatever that ‘it’ is: saying yes to that job, quitting a shitty one, breaking up with that man-child or telling someone special that you do care about them.

This photo is not about Skydiving. This photo is a memory that trusting your own abilities feels so damn good.

SHOT & EDITED BY @jacob using his ‘heli jump’ preset available at @aggiepresets #aggielook

#helijump #helicopter #skydiving #skydive #🪂🚁 #skydivewarszawa #heli

node.text:
I forgot to wear my jewelry, but I didn’t forget to wear my no fsss given attitude 💪🏼

The day of this event I spent the entire day cramped like sardines into a small plane with 20 other men.  I look at this photo and think about all the things I could’ve done to look even better that night. My bangs are too long, my jewelry is missing. My ‘look’ definitely wasn’t ‘perfect’ in my head but no one probably even noticed!

The old me would not go throwing herself out of plane for a whole day before an event because the old me derived her confidence from ‘looking good’.

Funk, God only knows how many days of my life were planned around washing my hair!!! The problem with that is there’s always gonna be someone prettier and with cleaner hair 😅 

When I gave up on ‘myself’ to then look ‘more perfect’ (by not swimming in the ocean or not going on a hike because of a shoot or an event) I left the experience looking beautiful but feeling like I betrayed myself.

The new me derives her confidence from being true to herself. And doing whatever the hell I want, even with that means having dirty hair 😜 and never apologizing for it.

Yes, it annoys me that the next day gossip magazines only write about the best dressed woman at the event instead adding others as the most fulfilled or confident ones. Or the best moms. Best partners. One that gives zero funks. But to be honest who cares what they say 😅🤷🏼‍♀️. What matters is how I feel about myself.

And I felt like a boss because of my relationship with myself that day. I didn’t give up on my passion so that I can wow total strangers with my ‘look’. And that made me more beautiful than wearing any jewelry.

Dream Dress: @kujawa.patrycja_designer
Hair @soulhair_by_sandrakpodonou 
Makeup @karinawaclawik #warszawa #warsaw #poland #confidence

node.text:
I miss ‘home’ — how amazing to hear 20,000 brothers and sisters rocked up to Black Rock City this week regardless of Burning Man being ‘cancelled’. I miss being in the city of Love & Kindness 😫

The first photo is extra special: I not only call BM home but also the US. This week marks 8 years living in California and I’m beyond grateful for all the dreams the country has allowed me to make happen.

I arrived in America with $525 in my pocket, single and with zero support from my family. I slept on a girlfriend’s couch for 7 months.

Yesterday, almost in the 8th year anniversary, I got nominated as American Influencer of the Year in the Travel category.

It might not be a big deal for many, but for an immigrant like myself it means the world.

Choosing your home is powerful. Don’t stay in a place that feels anything less than 100% you.

#burningman #burningman2021 #usa

node.text:
There was a moment (that lasted a couple of years 😜) when I hated Instagram. I didn’t even like a lot of my photos. I missed candid, ‘real’ photos caught in the moment which are hard to do when it’s just the two of you and need to set up a tripod or ask someone.

Recently, we realized we want take photos of us that would look dope in our house, not dope on Instagram. We changed our focus. We decided to create Something our kids would look at and get to know us a little more. Ones Full of life. Candid. Joyful. Not Instagrammy as much.

The way we do it is we rest the camera inside a shoe or a chair and set it to take photos every two seconds. We leave it there for a minute or for twenty. It depends. But we try not to think about it and just do our thing and focus on ourselves.

We might end up with a lot of blurry photos and some definitely not for Instagram 😅😜but there are still some that are just sooo us. And I love them. Like these 😍

Can’t wait to back home with you baby ❤️

@aggiepresets #positano #amalfi #italy #love #candid

node.text:
We definitely woke up some hills with the subtle sound of music coming out of our @lamborghini #Urus that came in an equally subtle color of Arancio Borealis (aka bright orange) 😜

Side note: I love road trips. I love that Jacob loves them too. Yes, this time in Dolomites we got to drive our dream car, but next week we’re jumping into a camper van and hitting the road again.

A car is a means to our goal, which is the lifestyle of exploring, the great outdoors and adventure. 

Not a goal in itself. I hope that despite us getting genuinely hyped about the tech and speed in Urus you can tell the difference 🤞🏼 

thank you @lamborghini for our dream road trip!!!

#dolomites #lamborghini #lamborghiniurus #italy #adventure

node.text:
I used to have a sexy back until today ( 😫SWIPE YO SEE!)— it’s funny because this morning J and I were listening to a motivational podcast at the gym (we connect to two sets of AirPods and work out at two different parts of the gym and then chat about what we listened to 💪🏼).

@tombilyeu said that he has an identity of a learner, which his ego doesn’t like. His ego likes being good at something. His identity of a learner involves really sucking at some thing for a long time and looking ridiculous which are mutually exclusive. That’s why he’s OK to suck at something.

I love and hate training. This morning NOTHING I DID worked. I sucked balls for an hour. Wind tunnel is Super fun but also super hard. But my identity as a learner will keep me going😅💨 

To all the learners out there — never stop ✋ love you!!! #amalfi #aggiepresets #aggielook

node.text:
Wanna know one of the most important rules in our relationship? It involves 💋+🧘‍♂️.

It’s the ‘50 kisses a day rule’. Proper Kissing and sex is obviously super important but that’s not what this rule is about (in fact, I don’t think it’s healthy to set a number of times a week to have sex thb).

Anywayssss 😅 a few months ago we realized that non-sexual kisses: weather they are on the forehead, a cheek, neck or head make us both feel super loved, cherished, adored and TRULY
SEEN. They aren’t meant to lead to anything, because if they did sometimes the other person might not be in the right space to get into some action and might not want to receive them 😉

They are meant to be given freely throughout the day to remind the other person that he or she is seen and their presence is noticed and that they are loved also non-sexually just because they are a human being with a soul.

I call them ‘namaste kisses’ — meaning: I bow to the light in you because it’s also within me’ ☀️ 

What rules do you have in your relationship?

🇵🇱 kochani ciekawa jestem ile osób doczyta do końca jeśli tak to napiszcie w komentarzu 😜

#couple #positano #chezblack #eataly
#italy #wlochy #travelcouple  #amalfi
